'''Berlin Raceway''' is a 0.438 mile long paved oval rac etrack in , near . It opened in 1950. The track is notable for the lack of an outside wall on the back straightaway, a unique feature for a national series such as . In addition, the short straights make it feel almost circular.
It is a stop on the ARCA and the  tour. The track was also a stop on the  tour before the series folded.
